meanings.definition: Not chosen for a position or office by vote
meanings.sent1: The nonelect candidate graciously accepted the outcome.
meanings.sent2: She was disappointed to be nonelect for the leadership role.
meanings.sent3: The nonelect team captain still cheered on her teammates.
meanings.sent4: The nonelect student council member continued to contribute ideas.
meanings.sent5: Being nonelect didn't diminish his enthusiasm for the cause.

meanings.definition: A person who has not been elected to a position or office
meanings.sent1: The nonelect was supportive of the elected officials.
meanings.sent2: As a nonelect, she focused on community service.
meanings.sent3: The nonelect joked about running for office next year.
meanings.sent4: The nonelect stood out for his dedication to the community.
meanings.sent5: Being a nonelect didn't deter her from making positive changes.
